quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  37,145,Then We cast him upon a desolate shore in a state of serious illness
  37,146,and caused a gourd plant to grow over him
  37,147,Then We sent him to a nation of one hundred thousand people or more
  37,148,"They believed in him, so We permitted them to enjoy their life for a while"
  37,149,"Just ask the unbelievers: Does it make any sense that their Lord should have daughters while they choose to have sons"
  37,150,Or is it that We created the angels as females and they were present at their creation
  37,151,Surely they invent a lie when they say
  37,152,Allah has children. They are utter liars
  37,153,Would He choose daughters rather than sons
  37,154,What is the matter with you? How do you judge
  37,155,Will you not take heed
  37,156,Or do you have any proof of what you are saying
  37,157,Show us your scriptures if you are truthful
  37,158,They assert blood- relationship between Him and the jinns; and the jinns know quite well that they will be called to account
  37,159,Glory be to Allah! He is free from what they ascribe to Him
  37,160,except His sincere devotees who do not attribute such things to Him
  37,161,Therefore neither you nor those whom you worship
  37,162,can deceive anyone about Allah
  37,163,except him who is destined for hell
  37,164,"The angels in fact say: \"We each have our appointed place"
  37,165,We range ourselves in ranks for His service
  37,166,and we are surely those who declare His glory
  37,167,"Before this, the same disbelievers used to say"
  37,168,If we had received a reminder which the earlier people had received
  37,169,We certainly would have been sincere devotees of Allah
  37,170,"But now that the Qur’an has come, they reject it: but soon they will find out the consequences of this attitude"
  37,171,We have already promised Our servants whom We sent as Messengers
  37,172,that they would certainly be helped
  37,173,and that Our forces will surely be victorious
  37,174,So give no heed to them for a while
  37,175,you will see their downfall as they shall see your victory
  37,176,Do they wish to hurry on Our punishment
  37,177,"But dreadful will be that morning, when it will descend in the courtyards of those who have been forewarned"
  37,178,So pay no heed to them for a while
  37,179,You will surely see their downfall as they shall see your victory
  37,180,"Glory be to your Lord, the Lord of Honor, He is free from what they ascribe to Him"
  37,181,Peace be on the Messengers
  37,182,"and praise be to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds"
  38,1,Suad
  38,2,And by the Qur’an which is full of admonition! Surely the unbelievers are in sheer arrogance and perverseness
  38,3,"How many generations have We destroyed before them? When their doom approached, they all cried out for mercy, but it was no longer the time to be saved"
  38,4,"They wonder that a Warner has come to them from among themselves, and the disbelievers say: \"He is a sorcerer telling lies"
  38,5,Does he claim that there is only One God in place of all other gods? Surely this is a strange thing
  38,6,"Their leaders go about saying: \"Pay no heed, stand firm in the service of your gods; this slogan of One God is designed against you"
  38,7,"We have not heard such a thing from anyone of the people of latter days (Jews and Christians): it is nothing but a fabrication"
  38,8,"Is he the only fit person among us to whom the admonition is revealed?\" But in fact they doubt My admonition, for they have not yet tasted My punishment"
  38,9,"Do they have the treasures of the mercy of your Lord, the All-Mighty, the Munificent One"
  38,10,"Or do they have sovereignty over the heavens and the earth and all that lies between them? If so, let them ascend by any means to be in a position of dictating to Allah according to their wishes"
  38,11,Their faction is no more than an army who will be beaten right here
  38,12,"Before them the people of Noah, `Ad and Pharoah, the man of stakes, denied their Messengers"
  38,13,"So did Thamud, the people of Lot and those of Aiykah (the people of Median) - all divided themselves into factions"
  38,14,"all charged their Messengers liars, so just was my torment of annihilating them"
  38,15,These people also await nothing but a single mighty Blast - the one which none may retard
  38,16,"They say: \"Our Lord, hasten our doom for us before the Day of Reckoning"
  38,17,"O Prophet, have patience at what they say, and remember Our servant David, the man of strength, who was frequent in turning to Allah for guidance"
  38,18,We made the mountains join him in Our praises at evening and the sunrise
  38,19,"And the birds, too, with all their flocks, join in singing with him"
  38,20,We strengthened his kingdom and gave him wisdom and sound judgment in speech and decision